	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok. I&#8217;ll keep this short and sweet.<BR>
<BR>
The dude that said pets suck at this level is right. They suck. For him.  If you don&#8217;t want to know what pets are for &#8211; please do not read any further. <BR>
<BR>
Remember when you were 10-15 level SK and hanging in Oasis whacking dervs?  Or a troll in the swamp waiting for a skelly to respawn?  Did you use a pet then? Yep? Why?  Let&#8217;s list the reasons. <BR>
<BR>
1. A pet is not a tank. A pet is a DOT with hit points!  (damage over time). It&#8217;s a DOT with attitude. <BR>
2. If you&#8217;ve got a chanter  - please do the group a favor and tell your pet to  get lost  - cause it&#8217;s  gonna hit the wrong mob at the wrong time and piss everyone off.<BR>
3. If you are in a party or fighters &#8211; your pet is not going to be very effective. However it makes excellent cannon fodder for when you all have to  run like blazes &#8216;cause you cant kill the mob and someones got to go down. <BR>
4. Make a pet and Med in peace. I&#8217;ll share a story with you &#8211; true one too- I&#8217;m in Oasis heading to a derv group.  I see a necro medding (or sitting, - heck he might&#8217;ve been playing card or even drunk)  the point is this. A puma walked up.. Whack. Pet killed the little bugger. I doubt the necro even noticed it was there.  Point is  - if it was a warrior regaining hp. He would have to get up . whack puma . chase puma kill puma find spot and start resting. You just sit and laugh while your pet kills stuff. <BR>
5. Solo with pets but use your brain and use one when you need to. The shmo that said his level 13 pet couldn&#8217;t kill anything in the Overthere is a brilliant guy.  I would like anyone level 13 to walk into the overthere with a rusty short sword totally naked and try to assist a warrior. Tell me your success rate.  The thing is we are a tank with pets and basically offensive spells.  We rock! <BR>
6. To be honest, I almost always use a pet once I have a group. (except for the above mentioned chanter scenario)  The extra damage doesn&#8217;t hurt. I&#8217;ve never had a group complain pets take exp. Most understand the pet is there to help and adds a bit of damage and is a good sacrificial lamb. <BR>
7. At 18th level now my pet has bash. I have bash. That&#8217;s 2 bashes. That&#8217;s 2 times I can keep that caster from casting (theoretically). A clerics stun spell doesn&#8217;t always work (neither does bash) but it&#8217;s still one more hit. Since I&#8217;m not that high I can&#8217;t speak for the higher level pets.  <BR>
8. Pets are cool. A SK does not have near the damage potential of a warrior at low levels.  However the warrior has this big empty mana bar. He gets to punch , kick, bash and do all those incredibly interesting warrior things.  We get a pet. We get to suck monsters dry to replenish our hit points. We need a cleric when it&#8217;s convenient for us.  We can DOT,  fear, snare (darkness)  and just have loads of fun. Shadowstep is KEWL.  <BR>
<BR>
Well that&#8217;s it for now. Have a great one. <BR>
<BR>
Mawl <BR>
Troll SK <BR>
The Nameless<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
